maml:description.maml:para:
A [System.Collections.Hashtable] value of each Interconnect Bay. Accepted values are:
* FlexFabric - HP VC FlexFabric 10Gb/24-Port Module * Flex10 - HP VC Flex-10 Enet Module * Flex1010D - HP VC Flex-10/10D Module * Flex2040f8 - HP VC FlexFabric-20/40 F8 Module * VCFC20 - HP VC 8Gb 20-Port FC Module * VCFC24 - HP VC 8Gb 24-Port FC Module * FEX - Cisco Fabric Extender for HP BladeSystem
E.g. @{1 = "Flex10";2 = "Flex10";3 = "FlexFabric";4 = "Flexfabric";5 = "";6 = "";7 = "";8 = "";}

QoS Traffic Classifier Object

 @{ 
 	qosTrafficClass = [PSCustomObject]@{

 		maxBandwidth     = 100;
 		bandwidthShare   = "0";
 		egressDot1pValue = 0;
 		realTime         = $false;
 		className        = "Class";
 		enabled          = $false;

     };

 	qosClassificationMapping = [PSCustomObject]@{

 		dot1pClassMapping = @();
 		dscpClassMapping  = @()

 	}

 }

A collection of LogicalDisk configuration objects. Can be created manually or with the New-HPOVServerProfileLogicalDisk helper Cmdlet.
[System.Array] @( [PSCustomObject]@{
[System.Bool]bootable - Indicates if the logical drive is bootable or not. [System.String]driveName - The name of the logical drive. [System.String]driveTechnology - Defines the interface type for drives that will be used to build the logical drive. Supported values depend on the local storage capabilities of the selected server hardware type. [System.String]raidLvel - The RAID level of the logical drive. Supported values depend on the local storage capabilities of the selected server hardware type [System.Int32]numPhysicalDrives - The number of physical drives to be used to build the logical drive. The provided values must be consistent with the selected RAID level and cannot exceed the maximum supported number of drives for the selected server hardware type.
} )

Optional. Array of Storage Volume resources to attach. Can be created by using the New-HPOVServerProfileAttachVolume Cmdlet. This parameter does not accept a Storage Volume resource from the Get-HPOVStorageVolume Cmdlet.
The format of the Storage Volume resource should be a PsCustomObject PowerShell resource with the following keys and values:
[PsCustomObject]@{ [System.Int]id - Valid Host LUN ID 0-254 [System.String]lunType - Auto or Manual [System.String]volumeUri - URI to Storage Volume that has been created and not assigned to another Server Profile if it is a Private Volume. [System.String]volumeStoragePoolUri - URI to HP OneView managed Storage Pool [System.String]volumeStorageSystemUri - URI to HP OneView managed Storage System [System.Array]storagePaths - Array specifying the Profile FC Connection ID associated with the path to the attached volume, and if the path is enabled or disabled. @( [System.Int]connectionId - FC Connection ID. If using New-HPOVServerProfileAttachVolume helper Cmdlet, New-HPOVServerProfile will automatically determine the FC connection ID. [System.Boolean]isEnabled - Enable or disable the path ) }

command:example.dev:code:
PS C:\> $profileName = "Web Server 10"
PS C:\> $svr         = Get-HPOVServer "Encl1, Bay 1" -ApplianceConnection 'MyAppliance.domain.com'
PS C:\> $con1        = Get-HPOVNetwork "Net-41-A"  -ApplianceConnection 'MyAppliance.domain.com' | New-HPOVServerProfileConnection -connectionId 1
PS C:\> $con2        = Get-HPOVNetwork "Net-41-B" -ApplianceConnection 'MyAppliance.domain.com' | New-HPOVServerProfileConnection -connectionId 2
PS C:\> $params = @{
>>    name                = $profileName;
>>    assignmentType      = "server";
>>    server              = $svr;
>>    connections         = ($con1, $con2);
>>    ApplianceConnection = 'MyAppliance.domain.com'
>>    }
>>    
PS C:\> New-HPOVServerProfile @params | Wait-HPOVTaskComplete

PS C:\> $profileName = 'Hypervisor Cluster Node 1'
PS C:\> $server = Get-HPOVServer "Encl1, Bay 1" #Gen9 Server
PS C:\> $con1 = Get-HPOVNetwork "Net-41-A" -ApplianceConnection 'MyAppliance.domain.com' | New-HPOVServerProfileConnection -connectionId 1
PS C:\> $con2 = Get-HPOVNetwork "Net-41-B" -ApplianceConnection 'MyAppliance.domain.com' | New-HPOVServerProfileConnection -connectionId 2
PS C:\> $LogicalDisk = New-HPOVServerProfileLogicalDisk -Name 'My Local Disk' -RAID RAID1 -NumberofDrives 2 -DiskType SasSsd
PS C:\> $params = @{
>>    name                = $profileName;
>>    assignmentType      = "server"
>>    server              = $server;
>>    connections         = $con1, $con2
>>    manageboot          = $True;
>>    bootMode            = "UEFI";
>>    pxeBootPolicy       = "IPv4ThenIPv6";
>>    bootOrder           = "HardDisk";
>>    HideUnusedFlexnics  = $True;
>>    LocalStorage        = $True;
>>    Initialize          = $True;
>>    LogicalDisk         = $LogicalDisk;
>>    ApplianceConnection = 'MyAppliance.domain.com'
>>    }
>>    
PS C:\> New-HPOVServerProfile @params | Wait-HPOVTaskComplete

